<a href="pre3.htm"><img border="0" src="next.gif" width="26" height="26"></a></p>
<ul>
  <li><font size="6"><font face="Arial">What is a Component?</font><br>
    </font><font size="4"><br>
    </font><font size="5" face="Arial">A practical definition is that a 
    component is any piece of a software that you want to treat as a 
    standard-issue &quot;black box&quot; chunk of functionality at design-time.</font></li>
</ul>
<p>¡¡</p>
<ul>
  <li><font size="6" face="Arial">What does a Component do?</font><br>
    <font face="Arial" size="5"><br>
    It has various aspects of functionality, including&nbsp; compound documents, 
    custom controls, inter-application scripting, data transfer, and other 
    software interactions.</font><font size="5">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font></li>
</ul>
<p>¡¡</p>
<ul>
  <li><font size="6" face="Arial">What language is a Component written?<br>
    </font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <font size="5" face="Arial">Components are written 
in different languages by different software vendors, <br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; in&nbsp; different parts of the&nbsp; world, and 
at different times.</font></p>

